 freestyle 120 kg|120kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[Ya\u015far Do\u011fu]] Tournament|Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships]] }}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Tournament|2019 Istanbul]] |[[2016 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2016 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Tournament|2016 Istanbul]]|[[2016 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2015 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships|2015 Istanbul]]|[[2015 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|2014 Istanbul|[[2014 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships - Men's freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships|2012 Ankara]]|[[2012 Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 120 kg|120kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[European Wrestling Championships|European Championships]] }}\n{{MedalGold|[[2012 European Wrestling Championships|2012 Belgrade]]|120kg}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2013 European Wrestling Championships|2013 Tbilisi]]|[[2013 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's Freestyle 120 kg|120kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2014 European Wrestling Championships|2014 Vantaa]] | [[2014 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|125kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2017 European Wrestling Championships|2017 Novi Sad]]|[[2017 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2018 European Wrestling Championships|2018 Kaspiysk]]|[[2018 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2019 European Wrestling Championships|2019 Bucharest]]|[[2019 European Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|125 kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[European Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold|[[Wrestling at the 2015 European Games|2015 Baku]] | [[Wrestling at the 2015 European Games \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|125kg]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Universiade]]}}\n{{MedalGold|[[2013 Summer Universiade|2013 Kazan]]|120kg}}\n| show-medals    = yes\n}}\n'''Taha Akg\u00fcl''' (born November 22, 1990 in [[Sivas]], Turkey) is an Olympic, World and European champion Turkish freestyle [[Sport wrestling|wrestler]] competing in the 125&nbsp;kg division. He is a student of physical education and sports at the [[Karamano\u011flu Mehmetbey University]] in [[Karaman]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.karamaninternet.com/kmu-ogrencisi-taha-akgul-avrupa-sampiyonu-oldu-2032h.htm |newspaper=Karaman \u0130nternet |title=KM\u00dc \u00d6\u011frencisi Taha AKG\u00dcL Avrupa \u015eampiyonu Oldu |date=March 10, 2012 |language=Turkish |accessdate=April 23, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nAkg\u00fcl took up wrestling in 2003 following his father and brother.<ref name=nbc/> He won the gold medal at the 40th [[Ya\u015far Do\u011fu]] International Wrestling Tournament held in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tgf.gov.tr/article.php?article_id=6532 |publisher=T\u00fcrkiye G\u00fcre\u015f federasyonu |title=40.Ya\u015far Do\u011fu Uluslararas\u0131 G\u00fcre\u015f \u015eampiyonas\u0131 Taha Akg\u00fcl Alt\u0131n Madalya Kazand\u0131\u011f\u0131 Ma\u00e7\u0131n G\u00f6r\u00fcnt\u00fcleri |language=Turkish |accessdate=April 23, 2012 }}</ref> At the [[2012 European Wrestling Championships]] held in [[Belgrade]], [[Serbia]], Taha Akg\u00fcl became champion in his weight category.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hurriyet.com.tr/spor/digersporlar/20085611.asp |newspaper=[[H\u00fcrriyet]] Spor |title=Taha Akg\u00fcl Avrupa \u015eampiyonu oldu |date=March 9, 2012 |language=Turkish |accessdate=April 23, 2012 }}</ref> He is now considered the best active wrestler with [[Abdulrashid Sadulaev]].\n\nHe qualified for the [[Wrestling at the 2012 Summer Olympics|2012 Olympics]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.haber7.com/haber/20120421/Taha-Akgul-olimpiyat-vizesi-aldi.php |newspaper=Haber 7 |title=Taha Akg\u00fcl, olimpiyat vizesi ald\u0131 |date=April 21, 2012 |language=Turkish |accessdate=April 23, 2012 }}</ref> He did not advance to quarterfinal after losing to [[Bilyal Makhov]] from Russia in the round of 16. At the 2012 World University Wrestling Championships held in [[Kuortane]], [[Finland]], he became gold medalist in his weight class.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.trtspor.com.tr/Haber.aspx?id=34917 |newspaper=TRT Spor |title=ASK\u0130 Spor'dan 3 madalya |date=October 8, 2012 |language=Turkish |accessdate=March 22, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130418181642/http://www.trtspor.com.tr/Haber.aspx?id=34917 |archivedate=April 18, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nTaha Akg\u00fcl defended his European champion title at the [[2013 European Wrestling Championships]] held in [[Tbilisi]], Georgia.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.sabah.com.tr/SabahSpor/TumSporlar/2013/03/21/taha-akgul-avrupa-sampiyonu |newspaper=[[Sabah (newspaper)|Sabah]] Spor |title=Taha Akg\u00fcl Avrupa \u015eampiyonu |date=March 21, 2013 |language=Turkish |accessdate=March 22, 2013 }}</ref> He won the bronze medal at the [[2013 World Wrestling Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 120 kg|2013 World Wrestling Championships]] in [[Budapest]], Hungary.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fila-official.com/sites/ultimate/index.php |publisher=FILA |title=2013 Senior World Championship \u2013 Men's freestyle 120kg |accessdate=September 18, 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130913093108/http://www.fila-official.com/sites/ultimate/index.php |archivedate=September 13, 2013 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014 and 2015 he won the world title in the 125&nbsp;kg division. In 2014 he selected as Best Wrestler of the Year by the Turkish Wrestling Federation.<ref name=nbc/> He won a gold medal at the 2016 Olympics defeating [[Komeil Ghasemi]] in the final.<ref name=rio/>\n\n==Wrestling record==\n{{s-start}}\n|-\n!  Res.\n!  Record\n!  Opponent\n!  Score\n!  Date\n!  Event\n!  Location\n|-\n|-\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=7 | [[2019 Turkey Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|2019 Turkey Championships]] {{gold1}} at 125&nbsp;kg\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|112\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} [[Tanju Gemici]]\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|Tech Fall (10\u20130)\n|style=\"font-size:88%\" rowspan=5|December 22, 2019\n|style=\"font-size:88%\" rowspan=5|[[2019 Turkey Championships \u2013 Men's freestyle 125 kg|2019 Turkey Championships]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;font-size:88%;\" rowspan=5|{{flagicon|TUR}} [[Ankara]]\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|111\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} H\u00fcseyin Civelek\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|Tech Fall (10\u20130)\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|110\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} Mustafa Tayyip K\u00fc\u00e7\u00fck\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|Tech Fall 10\u20130\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|109\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} Enes Kaan\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|Tech Fall 12\u20132\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|108\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|TUR}} Adil Misirci\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|Tech Fall (10\u20130)\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=7 | [[2019 Bundesliga \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|2019 Bundesliga tournament]] {{gold1}} at 125&nbsp;kg\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|107\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} Robin Ferdinand\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|19\u20134\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|November 16, 2019\n|style=\"font-size:88%\" rowspan=4|[[2019 Bundesliga Tournament_\u2013_Men%27s_Freestyle_125_kg|2019 Bundesliga Tournament]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;font-size:88%;\" rowspan=4|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Hockenheim]]\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|106\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} Nico Graf\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|16\u20130\n|style=\"font-size:88%\" rowspan=3|RKG Reilingen-Hockenheim\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|105\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|GER}} Alexander Kleer\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"| 16\u20130\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=7 | [[2019 Military World Games \u2013 Men's Freestyle 125 kg|2019 Military World Games]] {{gold1}} at 125&nbsp;kg\n|-\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|104\u20134\n|align=left|{{flagicon|IRI}} Yadollah Mohebbi\n|style=\"font-size:88%\"|3\u20130\